        "bio": "Josh and Cecil Wroten grew up in the Silicon Valley. They met in high school and later married in June of 2000. After graduating in May of 2002 from Trinity Baptist College in Florida, they returned to the Bay Area to start Morning Star Church in Newark. They have a vision to develop a multi-ethnic church community where people can find real answers to life&#39;s problems. They have been blessed with two children, Alanna Joy and Ethan Luke. Josh has a Master of Divinity degree from Golden Gate Seminary.<br /><br />Josh also serves as the Director of Church Planting for Next Generation Churches of Northern California and Nevada (www.nextgenchurches.com). He loves encouraging church planters to maintain a healthy balance between ministry, family, and spiritual life. Locally, he serves on the board for CityServe, the tri-cities association of pastors and churches that are committed to meeting the needs of the community in the name of Jesus.",
