        "bio": "As a San Francisco Bay Area resident all his life, Pastor David Clift knows both the stresses and opportunities that afford us in the East Bay. Born and raised in Concord, David grew up in what was a very functional home. He fought with his brother and two sisters, argued with his parents, and often struggled in school. Life was good. Life was &quot;normal.&quot; Then in 1972, when David was 10, life changed. David&#39;s family had never gone to church much, but someone invited them one Sunday and they heard a message that would change their lives forever.  David that heard that Jesus died and rose for him and that he could be forgiven for all of his wrong and become part of God&#39;s family simply by accepting what Jesus had done. David became a follower of Christ and life took an exciting turn. David prayed about what God would have him do with his life.  Since he was very young, David had always dreamed of being a lawyer, but by his junior year of high school, he knew God wanted him to pastor. David went on to college to earn a BA in Bible and a BA in Speech. Grad school led him to an MA in Biblical Studies and an MDiv. While in graduate school, David met his wife at a church in Martinez, where he was an Associate Pastor.  About four months after Cindy and David became engaged, Hillside Baptist Church (Hillside Church) contacted David and asked if he would consider coming as their pastor.  The church had declined and was deeply concerned for their welfare.  David came in September of 1989 and Cindy and David were married in October of 1989.  David continues as lead pastor.  David and Cindy now have three amazing daughters.  David enjoys running, kick boxing, water sports, snow skiing, and travelling.  Most of all, he loves sharing the greatest message of all with people.",
