        "bio": "My wife, Leighton, and I grew up, went to school, were married, and had our first child in Lexington, Kentucky. We moved to San Jose, California in February, 1977 with our first child just barely over one year old. Since then we have had three additional children and now have seven grandchildren. I joined the pastoral staff of Kingsway in 1981 and became the senior pastor in 1990. Leighton has been an Art teacher at Valley Christian High School for over twenty years and enjoys the rare opportunities she gets from time to time to do her own artwork. When our schedules permit, we have fun taking rides on our Harley Davidson. We have logged thousands of miles together with our most memorable trips being the old Route 66 from Chicago to Santa Monica and a trip to Sturgis, South Dakota for Bike Week after visting of the Grand Tetons and Yellowstone National Park. Our passion is to create an atmosphere of family as we build Christian community with our friends at Kingsway. We believe God is just as active in the world today as He was when the church was first born over two thousand years ago. His Holy Spirit is still working to transform lives, marriages, families, neighborhoods, and whole communities.",
