        "bio": "We began this new church/mission as Bible study at Java Shop in San Francisco, Ca. The owners were professional Latin Jazz Artists and asked if I would bring a few guys from our Church to have a little coffee, some live music and a Bible Study.  People liked it so much, hearing the Jazz, Gospel and Blues they thought it was a night club. It became a church after one year. I had been in the ministry in San Jose, Ca. for over 20 years at the same church.  We knew right away God was taking us to a new place with a new approach that was outside of the box. We changed our dress code to everyday clothes; Jeans, Levi&#39;s and comfortable clothes, so that the people in the City would not feel they had to wear a suit, which in the Mission District most people did not have.  The Java Shop was located in the Mission District on 24th. and Potrero Ave. We named it &#39;THE MISSION 24&#39; and our focus turned to people from the streets, those that were on drugs and homeless.  Our motto is &#39;Come to Jesus not Religion&#39; Come as you are! Matthew 11:28.  I have four children ages from 11, 12, 14 and 25 been married for 26 years to my wife Rebecca. Since the beginning our Gospel Blues Band has played through out California at Bike and Car shows, Rely for Life Cancer Walk and for 6 Time World Boxing Champion Robert the Ghost Guerrero home coming in Gilroy, Ca. We also are very connected to CROSS Ministries: a motorcycle club based in Gilroy, Ca. We ride to events and outreaches in several communities across the bay area.  We use the Motorcycles as a tool to meet people on the streets and bring Jesus to them.",
